<BaseLayout
  title="About FishSmithLake.com — Independent Fishing Resource"
  description="FishSmithLake.com is an independent fishing guide for Lewis Smith Lake, Alabama. Learn about our mission, our sources, and how we partner with local experts."
>
  <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1rem;">
    <h1 style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; font-size: 2.5rem; color: #2D6A4F; margin-bottom: 1rem;">About FishSmithLake.com</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: #7A9A7A; margin-bottom: 2rem;">An independent fishing resource built for Lewis Smith Lake anglers.</p>

    <div class="prose-lake">
      <p>FishSmithLake.com exists because Lewis Smith Lake deserves better than generic fishing advice. This lake — Alabama's deepest, spanning three counties in the north-central part of the state — is a world-class fishery that rewards anglers who understand its quirks. The crystal-clear water demands lighter tackle. The steep bluffs and submerged timber hold fish in ways a standard Alabama impoundment doesn't. The stripers run in different patterns than anywhere else in the state.</p>

      <p>We built this site to give Smith Lake anglers — from first-timers who just bought a boat to tournament regulars who've fished here for decades — a single reliable resource for the lake-specific information that matters.</p>

      <h2>What We Cover</h2>
      <p>Every page on FishSmithLake.com is written with Lewis Smith Lake specifically in mind. We cover:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Species guides for spotted bass, striped bass, crappie, and catfish</li>
        <li>Best fishing spots and coves across all three arms of the lake</li>
        <li>Seasonal fishing reports and timing guides</li>
        <li>Current water level information and how drawdowns affect fishing</li>
        <li>Alabama fishing license requirements and Smith Lake regulations</li>
        <li>Public boat launches and marinas across Cullman, Walker, and Winston counties</li>
        <li>Gear and lure recommendations tuned to Smith Lake's clear-water conditions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our Local Partners</h2>
      <p>Good lake knowledge comes from people who spend time on the water. We've partnered with local experts — including <strong>Justin Dyar</strong> at <a href="https://justindyar.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">justindyar.com</a> — to make sure the information on this site reflects real, current on-the-water experience.</p>

      <p>Justin has lived on Smith Lake for over 20 years. As the area's top-producing real estate broker for lakefront property, he's had the opportunity to fish virtually every corner of the lake and talk to hundreds of serious anglers about where the fish are and when. His insights inform several sections of this site, particularly the spots guides and the seasonal fishing breakdowns.</p>

      <h2>Transparency</h2>
      <p>FishSmithLake.com is an independent editorial resource. We have no affiliation with Alabama Power, the Alabama Department of Conservation and Natural Resources, or any government agency. We are not an official Smith Lake tourism site.</p>

      <p>This site does participate in the Amazon Associates program and may contain affiliate links to fishing gear. When you purchase through those links, we earn a small commission at no additional cost to you. Those commissions help us keep the lights on and the content updated. We only recommend gear that's actually worth buying for Smith Lake fishing.</p>

      <p>We also work with local businesses and service providers — like Justin Dyar's real estate practice — who provide value to people who love Smith Lake. Those relationships are disclosed where relevant.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Have a tip, a correction, or a question? Reach us on the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. If you've got great local knowledge about Smith Lake fishing, we want to hear from you.</p>
    </div>
